# Prefer shadcn/ui Components Over Custom or Third-Party Alternatives

## Context
shadcn/ui provides a comprehensive collection of beautifully designed, accessible, and fully-featured React components. These components are built on top of Radix UI primitives and styled with Tailwind CSS, ensuring consistency, accessibility, and proper theming integration.

Building custom components or importing third-party libraries when shadcn/ui equivalents exist leads to:
- **Inconsistent design** that doesn't follow the established design system
- **Missing accessibility features** that shadcn components provide by default
- **Theming conflicts** that don't integrate with the project's dark/light mode
- **Duplicate functionality** that increases bundle size and maintenance overhead
- **Lost integration benefits** like proper CSS variable usage and responsive design

## Rule
1. **Always check shadcn/ui first** before implementing custom UI components or importing third-party UI libraries.
2. **Use shadcn components** for all common UI patterns: buttons, cards, dialogs, forms, navigation, layouts, feedback (toasts), data display, etc.
3. **Install missing shadcn components** using `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` rather than building custom alternatives.
4. **When a third-party library is needed** (e.g., for specialized functionality), check if shadcn provides an integrated wrapper first.
5. **Only build custom components** when shadcn/ui genuinely lacks the required functionality and no suitable alternative exists.

## Available shadcn/ui Components
Common components that should always be preferred:

**Feedback & Communication:**
- `alert` - Alert messages and notifications
- `toast` - Toast notifications (wraps sonner with theming)
- `sonner` - Advanced toast notifications with full theming
- `alert-dialog` - Confirmation and alert dialogs
- `dialog` - Modal dialogs and overlays

**Forms & Input:**
- `button` - All button variants and states
- `input` - Text inputs with proper styling
- `textarea` - Multi-line text input
- `select` - Dropdown selection
- `checkbox` - Checkbox inputs
- `label` - Form labels

**Layout & Navigation:**
- `card` - Content containers
- `sheet` - Slide-out panels and drawers
- `sidebar` - Navigation sidebars
- `breadcrumb` - Navigation breadcrumbs
- `separator` - Visual dividers

**Data Display:**
- `badge` - Status indicators and labels
- `progress` - Progress bars
- `skeleton` - Loading placeholders
- `table` - Data tables

## Examples
| ❌ Bad (custom/third-party) | ✅ Good (shadcn/ui) |
|------------------------------|---------------------|
| ```tsx
// Custom toast implementation
import toast from 'react-hot-toast';
toast.success('Success!');
``` | ```tsx
// Use shadcn's sonner integration
import { toast } from "sonner";
toast.success('Success!');
// + Add <Toaster /> from @/components/ui/sonner to layout
``` |
| ```tsx
// Third-party modal library  
import Modal from 'react-modal';
<Modal isOpen={open}>Content</Modal>
``` | ```tsx
// Use shadcn dialog
import { Dialog, DialogContent } from "@/components/ui/dialog";
<Dialog open={open}>
  <DialogContent>Content</DialogContent>
</Dialog>
``` |
| ```tsx
// Custom button component
const CustomButton = ({ children, variant, ...props }) => (
  <button className={`btn ${variant}`} {...props}>
    {children}
  </button>
);
``` | ```tsx
// Use shadcn button
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
<Button variant="outline">Click me</Button>
``` |
| ```tsx
// Building custom card layout
<div className="border rounded-lg p-4 shadow">
  <h3 className="font-bold">Title</h3>
  <p>Content</p>
</div>
``` | ```tsx
// Use shadcn card
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card";
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>Content</CardContent>
</Card>
``` |

## Integration Benefits
Using shadcn/ui components provides automatic:
- **Theme integration** - Respects light/dark mode and CSS variables
- **Responsive design** - Mobile-first responsive behavior
- **Accessibility** - ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, screen reader support
- **Type safety** - Full TypeScript definitions and IntelliSense
- **Consistency** - Unified design language across the application

## Checklist for the Assistant
- [ ] Before suggesting custom UI components, check if shadcn/ui has an equivalent.
- [ ] When users need UI functionality, recommend the appropriate shadcn component first.
- [ ] If a shadcn component doesn't exist, suggest installing it with `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`.
- [ ] When third-party libraries are needed, check if shadcn provides an integrated wrapper (like sonner).
- [ ] Only suggest custom components when shadcn/ui genuinely lacks the required functionality.
- [ ] Always mention the integration benefits (theming, accessibility, consistency) when recommending shadcn components.
